    {
      "name": "Agreement",
      "description": "An Agreement is a contract, disregarding its status.\nA draft, a contract in progress, a negotiation, an executed document, a template are Agreements.\nYou can create, edit and share Agreements."
    },
    {
      "name": "Signature",
      "description": "Signature configuration related endpoints like auto-request and signature slots configuration. You can, for instance, add/remove slots, update their assignation, change orders."
    },
    {
      "name": "Automated Template",
      "description": "Once you have created an automated template in Concord,\nyou can then create and customize contracts to send out for collaboration and signature.\nYou can designate which content will be variable.\nVariables appear in blue in Concord and will be updated with data particular to each contract.\n\nMore information [here](https://help.concord.app/hc/en-us/articles/204428085-create-an-automated-template-with-excel)."
    },
    {
